Global Dental Implants & Prosthetics Market Insights
Dental Implants & Prosthetics Market size was valued at USD 10.75 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 15.18 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 4.4% from 2024 to 2030.

Dental Implants & Prosthetics Market Overview
The dental implants and prosthetics market is valued at approximately $12.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to grow at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030. This market encompasses the production, distribution, and use of dental implants, crowns, bridges, and other prosthetic components, which are crucial for replacing missing or damaged teeth. The growth in this sector is largely driven by increasing awareness of dental aesthetics, rising geriatric population, and technological advancements in dental procedures. Moreover, the global demand for cosmetic dentistry continues to rise, fostering strong market prospects.

